^-|ht|d|CP||FP||at|^B@2Many years ago there was a King who was powerful with vast knowledge to match his power and generosity. He took care of all his subjects who were mostly farmers. He gave them seeds to plant crops. The farmers were happy. There were plenty of food for all, The family size were large thanks to good and healthy environment--more babies being born each, year. The bulls were active and making calves frequently. All other live stocks were increasing in numbers. You can say that there was nothing to be concerned about.

Then one day the wise king was told of a new development in the neighboring kingdoms. The other Kings were giving the farmers the seed for crops which was treated with pesticides and fungicides in order to increase the crop size.

The king thought it was a great idea and adopted that policy. However,  farmers were happy and prosperous with Organic farming (the old fashion way)as they have done through many generations. Some started to question the change over.

Soon after the new policy went into effect the farmers began noticing the other side. The crop size increased but trouble started showing up everywhere. The Bulls were not interested-the number of calves dropped. The other live stocks were producing very few. The men farmers were too tired and their wives had headaches all the time. Everyone blamed all the added chemical to the seeds for their plight. 

An old farmer decided to present the problem to the King.  The other farmers tried to talk him out of doing so. "He will be dismayed and you may end up the rest of your life sleeping with the skunks old man." some warned him. The old farmer said, "The King is wise and kind. He loves his subjects and will not do such a thing."  But to be on the safe side he sent his grip to the King written on baked bricks called BBO movies.

The old farmer was right. The King in his wisdom saw the merits for both and decided henceforth he will give one half of the seed as before--organic--and the other half treated. That made many of his farmers happy. At least there were no more headaches or falling sleep early. Better yet the bulls started charging in the field. The Farmers in the adjoining kingdoms were hoping that their Kings would do the same.

Any similarity between this story from the past and recent events in BBO is purely accidental.|
